<h2 class="bac">Summary:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong A&ndash;level grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Working knowledge of Java and/or C++</li>
	<li>Primary locations: Opportunities in London, Croydon, Dublin, Geneva</li>
	<li>Desk&ndash;specific, 9&ndash;week programme from June &ndash; August</li>
	<li>Online application form</li>
	<li>Application Deadline: 17 December 2010</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
A culture of innovation is at the heart of everything we do. This stems from a commitment for continuous improvement and a desire to remain at the forefront of the world&#39;s financial markets. As technology evolves, the knowledge and skill set of associates within technology must also evolve, enabling us to continue to develop and deliver the multi&ndash;platform, multi&ndash;product range for which we are renowned. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The company&#39;s strategic vision is to deliver market&ndash;leading technology that drives our business forward. Our teams work very closely with our business partners, developing strategies and delivering solutions that are integral to the day&ndash;to&ndash;day running of our business. Technology embraces everything from sales, trading and research applications, trade processing, risk management, portfolio management, payment services, voice recognition, and quantitative and qualitative analysis, to security analytics, management reporting and stakeholder relationship management.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Summer Analyst Programme within Technology is a precursor to the Technology Analyst Full&ndash; Time Programme. As a Technology Analyst, you&#39;ll: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Work as a developer, tester, systems support analyst or business analyst within a fast&ndash;paced, innovative environment</li>
	<li>Have a rich and varied working experience </li>
	<li>Work closely with colleagues throughout our organisation to build relationships</li>
	<li>Gain the knowledge and expertise to meet the challenges critical to building a technology career within the financial services industry</li>
	<li>Be exposed to a broad range of technologies covering many diverse environments, including: 
        <ul>
	<li><b>Applications development</b> &ndash; involving the design, development and deployment of state&ndash;of&ndash;the&ndash;art applications using Java, C++, .NET and Web Services, to power and improve our business </li>
	<li><b>Business analysis</b> &ndash; using key client&ndash;facing skills and deep technical expertise to bridge business and technology and create powerful specifications </li>
	<li><b>Project and delivery management</b> &ndash; bringing new applications online using Waterfall and Agile development lifecycle methodologies</li>
        </ul></li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Strong academic qualifications are important, but you&#39;ll also need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a genuine interest in a technology career within financial markets.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
We accept applications from a diverse range of degree disciplines, although Computer Science and Engineering subjects are key for this line of business. Working knowledge of Java and/or C++ is essential. You&#39;ll also need teamwork, leadership and problem&ndash;solving skills, plus creativity, along with the ability to work in a fast&ndash;paced environment, multi&ndash;task and interact with a variety of people. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The best opportunity to learn about working life at the bank is to experience it first&ndash;hand through our nine&ndash;week Summer Programme. Aimed at students in their penultimate year, the programme runs from June to the end of August, and is designed to help you decide whether our offering matches your aspirations. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
You&#39;ll be assigned to one of our core technology groups that support our businesses, such as Wealth Management or Rates &#38; Currencies. Working on real tasks, problems, issues or projects, alongside our technologists, will give you a unique learning opportunity and exposure to life at a leading investment bank. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The programme includes: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Classroom instruction prior to assignment</li>
	<li>Senior Speaker Series, featuring presentations by top executives </li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior technologists and network with peers </li>
	<li>A mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
If you perform well during your time, you may go back to university with a job offer for the following year, enabling you to truly focus on your studies. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

